### Assign an isolation segment

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/spaces/[guid]/relationships/isolation_segment" \
  -X PATCH \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "data": {
      "guid": "[iso-seg-guid]"
    }
   }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :space_isolation_segment_relationship, '/v3/spaces' %>
```

This endpoint assigns an isolation segment to the space.
The isolatoin segment must be entitled to the space's parent organization.

<aside calss="notice">Apps will not run in the newly assigned isolation segment until they are restarted.</aside>

#### Definition
`PATCH /v3/spaces/:guid/relationships/isolation_segment`

#### Required Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
**data** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | Isolation segment relationship. Apps will run in this isolation segment. Set data to `null` to remove the relationship.

